               <floruit notBefore="1634" notAfter="1658">He was the traditional Ethiopian scholar and the main informant of the great scholar and father of Ethiopian studies <persName ref="PRS6378Ludolf">Ludolf</persName>,  
                  claimed to be a descendant of a famous Amhara  lineage from <placeName ref="LOC4461Makana">Makāna Śǝllāse</placeName>. 
               When <persName ref="PRS4767Gorgoryo">Gorgoryos</persName> converted to Catholic faith, the Jesuit patriarch 
                  <persName ref="PRS7002Mendes">Mendes</persName> appointed him as his secretary. Following the abdication of <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos">Susǝnyos</persName>, 
                  <persName ref="PRS4767Gorgoryo"><roleName type="title">ʾabbā</roleName> Gorgoryos</persName> fled to <placeName ref="Q220">Rome </placeName>,  in <date>1634</date>, where he met  
                  <persName ref="PRS6378Ludolf">Ludolf</persName>, in <placeName ref="Q46">Europe</placeName>.   
                     He taught <persName ref="PRS6378Ludolf">Ludolf</persName> Gǝʿǝz and Amharic.</floruit>
